deck: Expat from Hell and past lover of John Constantine.
description:
Origin

Very little is known about Blythe. A demon, they left Hell at some point and were able to negotiate a deal to remain on Earth. There, they got involved in the theatre and nightclub businesses.

Creation

Blythe was created by James Tynion IV, Ming Doyle and Riley Rossmo. They made their first appearance in Constantine: The Hellblazer #1.

Major Story Arcs

The Hellblazer

Blythe contacts their occasional lover John Constantine, claiming to need his help with an imp infestation in their theatre. Constantine agrees to assist, but, upon realising he is being used to remove Blythe's business partner Haluk, tricks Blythe into banishing themselves to Hell. Trapped there, Blythe encounters the captive Constantine and Papa Midnite, and offers to help them escape Hell, on the condition that they take Blythe with them. Constantine betrays them just before they escape, and Blythe immediately makes a deal with Neron to leave Hell and get revenge on Constantine. They orchestrate the kidnapping of John's boyfriend Oliver's children, and magically constrain Constantine from interfering in Neron's plans. They make a deal with Oliver in exchange for his children's souls, and drag Oliver to Hell when Constantine arrives, having just succeeded in finding another way to free the children.

Powers and Abilities

Blythe is a demon, and possesses a fair amount of magical power, as well as a great deal of knowledge about the occult and exorcism. They are very gifted at scheming and conniving, and have the demonic power to make deals for human souls. The have long, sharp talons, and sharp fangs, and seem to be fairly strong despite appearing quite spindly.
name: Blythe

deck: Business partner of Blythe at the soul-harvesting theatre Inferno
description:
Origin

Very little is known about Haluk. A demon, he left Hell at some point and became involved in the nightclub and entertainment industry. Despite warnings about their trustworthiness, he blackmailed the demon Blythe into becoming his partner in his newest venture, the theatre Inferno.

Creation

Haluk was created by James Tynion IV, Ming Doyle, and Riley Rossmo. He made his first appearance in Constantine: The Hellblazer #1.

Major Story Arcs

The Hellblazer

Haluk is confronted in his office by Blythe, who brought John Constantine as part of a hostile takeover of their shared business. Enraged, he attacks, and is banished to Hell by Constantine and Blythe.

Powers and Abilities

Haluk is a demon, and is able to grow greatly in size and become superhumanly strong when angered. He is fairly intelligent and conniving, and able to manage a business empire. Like all demons, he is able to make deals for human souls, and derives power from these deals.
name: Haluk
